            "summary": "A recent study reported that the global economy shrank by 4.3% in 2020 due to the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic. This marked the largest annual contraction in almost 75 years. The study also highlighted that global trade saw a 9.2% decline, while foreign direct investment fell by 42%. The pandemic led to a loss of 8.8% in global working hours equivalent to 255 million full-time jobs. Additionally, the global unemployment rate rose by 1.1% to 6.5%, with 114 million people losing their jobs. The study revealed that the largest economic setbacks were observed in the tourism and hospitality industries, as well as in manufacturing and retail sectors.Experts project that the global economy is set to recover by 5.6% in 2021, but this will be contingent on successful vaccination campaigns and policy support. The report emphasized the urgent need for international cooperation to address the ongoing economic challenges posed by the pandemic.",
